    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I think the state should be kept outside\r\n\r\nThe general state is easy to save, but the complexity is raising fast when starting to consider the inner components (E.g. some user typed token description in minting view, or the amount currently typed in the holdings dropdown.). One question here would be: Is it worth the effort to move the state outside of settings view?\r\n\r\nThe other options I see here are:\r\n1. to preserve the view once it's been loaded.\r\n2. A hybrid approach - Save the general state and unload the view **if** it's not dirty. Otherwise preserve the entire view.\r\n\r\nIMO would be nice to have the entire UI state saved when switching views because I personally find it a bad UX to discard the work in progress without notification.\r\n\r\n",
